he voice prize 2017\n* Danish Music Awards \u00c5rets Nyt\u00e6nker 2012\n* The voice \u00c5rets Flirt 2012\n* The voice The Body Art 2012\n* The voice \u00c5rets Instagrammmer 2013\n* Gaffa-prisen \u00c5rets Mandlige Kunstner 2014\n* Danish Music Awards Publikumsprisen 2014\n* Danish Music Awards \u00c5rets Danske popudgivelsen 2014\n* MTV Europe Music Awards for \u00e5rets danske band 2014\n* The voice \u00c5rets Trends\u00e6tter 2014\n* The Voice \u00c5rets Idol 2014\n* Danish Music Awards \u00c5rets Danske Club Navn 2014\n* Zulu Awards \u00c5rets Mandlige Kunstner 2015\n* The voice-pris 2015\n\n==Tours==\n*Colours Tour 2012-2013\n*Christopher Tour 2013\n*Told you So Tour 2014-2015\n*Tulips Tour 2015\n*Closer Tour 2016\n\n==References==\n{{reflist|30em}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{Official website|http://www.christophermusic.dk/}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Christopher}}\n[[Category:Danish male singers]]\n[[Category:English-language singers from Denmark]]\n[[Category:1992 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n\n[[Category:People from Frederiksberg]]\n[[Category:People from T\u00e5rnby Municipality]]\n[[Category:Singers from Copenhagen]]\n[[Category:21st-century Danish singers]]\n[[Category:21st-century male singers]]\n", "text_old": "{{Use mdy dates|date=December 2015}}\n{{BLP sources|date=February 2014}}\n{{Infobox musical artist\n| name = Christopher\n| background =  solo_singer\n| image = Christopher (sanger).jpg\n| image_size = 275px\n| caption =Christopher Live in 2012\n| birth_name =Christopher Lund Nissen\n| alias =\n| birth_date   = {{birth date and age|1992|01|31}}\n| birth_place  = [[Frederiksberg]], Denmark\n| origin       = [[Denmark]]\n| genre        = Pop      \n| occupation   = Singer and songwriter\n| instrument   = Vocal,guitar and piano\n| years_active = 2011{{spaced ndash}}present\n| label = EMI Denmark\n| associated_acts = [[Frida Amundsen]]<br>[[Molly Sand\u00e9n]]<br>[[Brandon Beal]]\n| website ={{URL|http://christophermusic.dk/}}\n| current_members =\n| past_members =\n}}\n'''Christopher Nissen''' (born January 31, 1992) is a Danish singer from Copenhagen, signed to EMI Denmark. In November 2012, he won an award at the [[Danish Music Awards 2012]]. He was awarded ''New Thinker of the Year'' (\u00c5rets nyt\u00e6nker), given by Spotify as an innovation prize.<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.mynewsdesk.com/dk/pressroom/emi-music-denmark/pressrelease/view/christopher-vinder-innovationspris-aarets-nytaenker-til-danish-music-awards-debutalbum-colours-genudgives-12-nov-med-nyt-materiale-811389 |title=Mynewsdesk.com |access-date=December 29, 2012 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20130129095343/http://www.mynewsdesk.com/dk/pressroom/emi-music-denmark/pressrelease/view/christopher-vinder-innovationspris-aarets-nytaenker-til-danish-music-awards-debutalbum-colours-genudgives-12-nov-med-nyt-materiale-811389 |archive-date=January 29, 2013 |url-status=dead }}</ref> Christopher released four albums, the debut ''[[Colours (Christopher album)|Colours]]'' (2012), followed by ''[[Told You So (Christopher album)|Told You So]]'' (2014), ''[[Closer (Christopher album)|Closer]]'' (2016) and ''Under the Surface'' (2019). Christopher's songs include \"[[Against the Odds (song)|Against the Odds]], \"[[Nothing in Common (Christopher song)|Nothing in Common]]\", \"[[Told You So (Christopher song)|Told You So]]\", \"CPH Girls\" and \"[[I Won't Let You Down (Christopher song)|I Won't Let You Down]]\".\n\n==Career==\nChristopher started singing covers of others' singer's songs. His debut single was \"[[Against the Odds (song)|Against the Odds]]\", co-written by Kay & Ndustry, Kasper Larsen, Ole Brodersen, Curtis Richa and Johan Wetterberg, and produced by Kay & Ndustry and GL Music's Lasse Lindorff.<ref>[http://www.glmusic.dk/news/christopher-against-the-odds.aspx GL Music: Christopher \u2013 'Against The Odds'] {{webarchive |url=https://web.archive.org/web/20111001015348/http://www.glmusic.dk/news/christopher-against-the-odds.aspx |date=October 1, 2011 }}</ref> It was released in September 2011, reaching number 23 on the Danish Singles Chart.<ref>[http://danishcharts.com/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Christopher+%5BDK%5D DanishCharts: Christopher page]</ref> The accompanying music video is directed by Nicolas Tobias F\u00f8lsgaard and Jonas Lodahl Andersen. His follow-up single \"[[Nothing in Common (Christopher song)|Nothing in Common]]\" entered the Danish Singles Chart at number 5 in 2012. His debut album ''[[Colours (Christopher album)|Colours]]'' was released in 2013. \"CPH Girls\" was Christopher's 1st single number one in Denmark. Christopher's third studio album ''[[Closer (Christopher album)|Closer]]'' came out on April 15, 2016. It includes his earlier hit \"Tulips\" that came out in Denmark, Norway and China, \"[[I Won't Let You Down (Christopher song)|I Won't Let You Down]]\" featuring [[Bekuh Boom]] becoming his second number 1 in Denmark and the track \"Limousine\" with the artist [[Madcon]]. Christopher gets his inspiration for [[Michael Jackson]], [[Justin Timberlake]], [[Bruno Mars]] and [[John Mayer]].\n\n==Personal life==\nHe was born in Frederiksberg, but later moved to Amager, Denmark with his parents and little brother Oliver.<ref>{{cite web|title=Christopher|url=http://www.seoghoer.dk/vipedia/christopher|website=Se og h\u00f8r|publisher=Aller Media A / S|accessdate=27 December 2015|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20151227142855/http://www.seoghoer.dk/vipedia/christopher|archivedate=December 27, 2015 |language=Danish}}</ref> In 2012  Christopher moved in with his girlfriend  the Danish singer [[Medina (singer)|Medina]]. The couple later split up. Since 2014 Christopher has been in a relationship with the Danish model Cecilie Haugaard. Today the couple lives in Amager on a property worth 6,720,000 Danish Kroner. Christopher and Cecilie Haugaard have been together for four years as of 2018. Since the beginning of June 2019 he is married to her.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.instagram.com/p/ByS-_-oAcIJ/|title=Christopher on Instagram: \u201cIt's hard to describe how magical this weekend was!! I can't wait to spend the rest of my life with this happy girl, I now get to call my\u2026\u201d|website=Instagram|language=en|access-date=2019-06-22}}</ref>\n\n<br />\n\n==Discography==\n===Albums===\n====Studio albums====\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders\" style=\"text-align:center;\"\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:10em;\"| Title\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:15em;\"| Details\n! scope=\"col\" colspan=\"1\"| Peak chart positions\n! scope=\"col\" rowspan=\"2\" style=\"width:12em;\"| [[List of music recording certifications|Certifications]]\n|-\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:3em;font-size:85%;\"| [[Tracklisten|DEN]]<br><ref name=\"den\">[http://danishcharts.dk/showinterpret.asp?interpret=Christopher+%5BDK%5D danishcharts.dk: Christopher Discography]</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Colours (Christopher album)|Colours]]''\n|\n* Released: March 19, 2012\n* Label: [[EMI]]\n* Format: [[Compact disc|CD]], [[music download|digital download]]\n| 4\n|\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Told You So (Christopher album)|Told You So]]''\n|\n* Released: March 24, 2014\n* Label: [[Parlophone]]\n* Format: CD, digital download\n| 2\n|\n* [[IFPI Denmark|IFPI DEN]]: Gold<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ifpi.dk/?q=content/christopher-told-you-so-1|title=Christopher \"Told You So\" (Album)|publisher=[[IFPI Denmark]]|accessdate=April 1, 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''[[Closer (Christopher album)|Closer]]''\n|\n* Released: April 15, 2016\n* Label: Parlophone\n* Format: CD, digital download\n| 1\n|\n* IFPI DEN: Gold<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ifpi.dk/?q=certificeringer&page=4|title=Certificeringer|publisher=IFPI Denmark|accessdate=July 17, 2018}}</ref>\n|-\n! scope=\"row\"| ''Under the Surface''\n|\n* Released: February 22, 2019\n* Label: Parlophone\n* Format: CD, digital download\n| 5\n|\n|}\n\n===Singles===\n====As